AGI - The President of the Republic of Sergio&nbsp;Mattarella opened the high-level conference on Peace, Justice and Social Inclusion. The Conference, which generally takes place at the agency Onu Idlo based in Rome, monitors the objective 16 of Agenda 2030 for sustainable development. This year the decision to organize it at the Glass Palace in the presence of the President &nbsp; Mattarella&nbsp; and with the moderation of the Italian ambassador to the United Nations Maurizio Massari, symbolizes the Italian commitment on the issues of the fight against organized crime and the levels of justice in the different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br> Among the other themes at the centre of Objective 16 of Agenda traffic and violence on children, corruption and rule of law. Thanks to Italy, in the name of Giovanni Falcone, as Mattarella recalled in his speech,&nbsp; on 21 March the resolution establishing the International Day for the prevention and fight of all forms of organised transnational crime was adopted at the UN. The first International Day will be celebrated on November 15 in New York and the related events will be organized by Italy.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Peace, inclusion, justice - said Mattarella - are indispensable cornerstones for the sustainable development of each country and every society and I like to emphasize how they are leading principles of the Italian constitutional order". "We make today - it has emphasized in another passage - an additional danger that undermines the relationship of trust with the institutions and between the countries: that of disinformation. On Friday, the World Press Freedom Day admonishes the value of freedom of information for the maintenance of democracy. Themes such as access to information, freedom of expression, protection of privacy, belong, in good law, to the goals included in Objective 16, the subject of this discussion". &nbsp; "With - and in - the United Nations - it has continued - we have to work to restore trust between nations, strengthen international cooperation and weave new networks of understanding and collaboration".
"It is on the basis of this approach - the President has remembered - that Italy unfolds its action, with firm determination to support the tools of dialogue based on that principle of multilateralism that today we see so dramatically questioned by Russian aggression to Ukraine and the consequences of the unsolved Israeli-Palestinian conflict".
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"We cannot continue to engage in relations between countries based on visions and 19th century heritage, on power drives" he added. Then, at the end of his speech, the President of the Republic, in a safety column formed by nine vehicles, left the Glass Palace to start another event, a gala lunch in which he will meet the Italian community.

