AGI - Russian President Vladimir Putin ordered the army to carry out nuclear weapons exercises > involving the Navy and troops based near Ukraine. The Defense Ministry announced it. "A number of measures will be taken during the exercise to prepare and use non-strategic nuclear weapons," said the Ministry of Defense. "During the exercise, a series of measures will be taken to train the preparation and use of non-strategic nuclear weapons," said the ministry in a note where he added that the measure was taken "on instructions of the commander-in-chief of the armed forces of the Russian Federation," Vladimir Putin.
&nbsp;
A move, according to Moscow, which aims to "maintain the readiness" of the army > to protect the country, "in response to provocative statements and threats against Russia by some Western officials", added the ministry. In October 2023, Russia announced that Vladimir Putin oversaw the launch of ballistic missiles during military maneuvers to simulate a "nuclear attack mass" in response to Moscow. During these exercises, an intercontinental ballistic missile Iars was launched by the Plesetsk cosmodrome, in the North of Russia, and another Sineva ballistic missile from a submarine in the Barents Sea.
&nbsp;
The imminent nuclear exercises announced by Russia are an answer to the comments "without precedent", in particular that of French President Emmanuel Macron>, on the sending of troops to Ukraine. "It is obvious that we are talking about the statements of Macron and the British representatives," said the Kremlin spokesman Dmitri Peskov when journalists asked him what had caused the exercises, adding: "This is a completely new phase of escalation of tensions. It is unprecedented and requires special measures. "
&nbsp;
<h2> Kiev drones kill six people in the Russian region of Belgorod</h2>
Ukrainian drones have attacked vehicles in the district of Borisovka, in the Russian region of Belgorod, causing 6 victims. The head of district administration Vladimir Pereverzev reported this in a regional government meeting. "Two vehicles carrying personnel to the pig farms of the Agro-Belogorye group were attacked today by drones. Thirty-three people were injured and six died," Pereverzev said.
&nbsp;
<h2> Ukraine, Borrell: the aim is to produce weapons in place with EU funds
"The EU and Ukraine defense industries gather here. We are over 140 companies from 25 different countries. And the goal is to couple the European defence capabilities and Ukraine > and see what opportunities are to use European funds to produce more and quickly. If possible directly in Ukraine. It is important that production be made in Ukraine, by Ukrainian companies, supported by the EU. We save transport costs and produce where it is needed." This was declared by the EU High Representative for Foreign Policy, Josep Borrell, upon his arrival at the meeting of the European and Ukrainian defence industry.

